Back to Basics - Kubernetes 

Kubernetes - A Container Orchestrator that allow you to manage, deploy and Scale Containerize application efficiently at Scale.


Container
A ready-to run software package containing everything needed to run an application; the code and any runtime it requires.
Cannot be deployed directly to physical or Virtual Hosts.

Pod 
Contains one or mode application containers
Contain Zero or more storage volumes
Smallest unit of deployment and scaling in Kubernetes.

Node
Contains one or more Pods.
Physical/virtual host provide compute resources.
Container runtime to retrieve container images and run containers.
Kubelet (agent to manage Pods in node and across nodes) 
Kube-Proxy (mange network between pods in node and across cluster)

Cluster 
Group of one or more nodes in Kubernetes environment.
Control plane orchestrates apps through Nodes and Pods.

